The paper deals with motion planning for robots in a planar environment cluttered with obstacles, which is a classic problem in robotics (cs.RO). The problem involves geometric computations and algorithms for finding optimal solutions, which are also relevant to computational geometry (cs.CG). The algorithm proposed in the paper involves graph theory and combinatorial optimization, which are topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DS) and algorithms and complexity (cs.DM). The paper also mentions the use of heuristics and optimization techniques, which are common in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
